The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Tamil Nadu attracts SEZ aspirants

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 New Delhi, Oct. 6: The commerce ministrys board of approval today took up 88 proposals for setting up special economic zones out of which eight were given formal clearance and 17 got in-principle approval. With todays decision, the total number of formal approvals has increased to 189 and in-principle approvals has gone up to 145, an official release said.

 While eight of the applications that were cleared are for Bengal, the major proposals for the rest of the country include an aluminium SEZ by Hindalco Industries to be set up on 2,025 hectares of land in Sidhi district of Madhya Pradesh, a Lotus Footwear (contract manufacturer for Nike Shoes) project in Tamil Nadu and a Suzlon Infrastructure proposal for a high-tech engineering equipment facility in Coimbatore.

 As many as 13 of the 25 proposals approved today are for SEZs to be set up in Tamil Nadu. Two proposals were for Madhya Pradesh and one for Rajasthan where Adani Exports wants to set up a multi-product zone on 1000 hectares in Alwar.

 These proposals will now go to the empowered group of ministers for final approval.




